verbLexeme: 1. To have a headache and a feeling of sickness in the morning because you have drunk a lot of alcohol the night before. English = have a hangover, (be) hungover.
nominalLexeme: 1. A headache and feeling of sickness that you have in the morning if you have drunk a lot of alcohol the night before. English = hangover.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: pulling on something around the neck.
